22/11/2002
PRAGUE, Czech Republic -- The presidents of Albania, Croatia and Macedonia met briefly Friday (22 November) with US President George W Bush at the NATO summit in Prague. Croatia's ambassador to the United States, Ivan Grdesic, said Bush supported the aspirations of the three countries to enter the alliance during the next enlargement wave. On Thursday, Croatian President Stipe Mesic, Albania's Alfred Moisiu and Macedonia's Boris Trajkovski met to discuss concrete, trilateral projects they could undertake to speed up their NATO integration. (HINA, HRT - 22/11/02; ATA - 21/11/02)
